# Update Docs on Application Changes

When adding or changing user-facing features (pages, workflows, UI, API behavior), **update the relevant documentation** before finishing.

## User Documentation

- **Location:** `frontend/content/user-guide/*.md`
- **Map changes to doc files:**
  - Overview, watchlist, anomalies, context banner → `monitoring-overview.md`
  - Simulator, streamer, ingest API → `connecting-streams.md`
  - Search, channel detail, LLM explanation → `investigating-channels.md`
  - Event Console, alerts, Ack/Resolve → `handling-alerts.md`
  - Source selector, multi-source, feed health → `multi-source.md`
  - New pages or major flows → `reference.md` or new workflow doc
- Keep content **workflow-focused**: describe cause-and-effect (e.g., "You connect a stream → Overview shows Live → ..."), not feature lists.

## Changelog

- **Location:** `CHANGELOG.md` at project root
- **Format:** [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) — use `Added`, `Changed`, `Fixed`, `Removed`, `Security`
- Add an entry for user-facing changes (features, fixes, breaking changes)
- Place new entries under `## [Unreleased]` at the top
